---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Editorial Responsibility | AILD"
  description="How AILD is edited, maintained, and reviewed as an executive-focused platform covering AI governance, rollout, and oversight."
  canonical="https://aild.org/author/"
  active="about"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Editorial Responsibility</p>
    <h1>How AILD is edited and maintained</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      AILD is maintained as an independent editorial platform for decisionmakers who need practical guidance on AI governance,
      rollout, oversight, and operating models.
    </p>
    <div class="badge-row">
      <span class="badge">Independent editorial platform</span>
      <span class="badge">Bilingual publishing</span>
      <span class="badge">Executive communication focus</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section about-grid">
    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Background</p>
      <h2>Editorial and publishing experience</h2>
      <p>
        AILD is informed by substantial experience across editing, publishing, websites, communications, and knowledge
        products, with an emphasis on turning complex topics into usable executive guidance.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Relevant lens</p>
      <h2>Executive communication, not generic AI commentary</h2>
      <p>
        The AILD lens is shaped by work on strategy communication, editorial systems, and decision-support publishing rather
        than by a general-purpose AI news model.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Why it matters</p>
      <h2>Readers need judgment, structure, and accountability</h2>
      <p>
        AILD is built to help leadership teams decide what to govern, what to test, what to measure, and what should remain
        under explicit human responsibility.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section split-callout">
    <div class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Role at AILD</p>
      <h2>What the editorial team is responsible for</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Selecting topics with executive relevance rather than trend-chasing value.</li>
        <li>Turning coverage into frameworks, checklists, templates, and working formats.</li>
        <li>Maintaining consistency across English and Chinese editorial tracks.</li>
        <li>Updating flagship pages when operating guidance changes meaningfully.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Trust links</p>
      <h2>How to evaluate AILD's work</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/editorial-standards/">Read the editorial standards and evidence policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="/research/">Review the research index and cited source categories</a></li>
        <li><a href="/about/">See the broader mission and positioning of AILD</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
